title: Auld licht idylls.
author: Barrie, J. M.
snippet: The struggle at Cabbylatch itself was not of long duration ; for their own horses proved the farmer's worst enemies, except in the cases where the sagacious animals took matters into their own ordering and bolted judiciously for their stables.
